<h3>Intro</h3>
<p>A44 (UCC) = DPSP , minority women most vulnerable =&gt; genuine sense of equal participation</p>
<p>SC judgement 2020 = Goa UCC = SC said it is&nbsp;<strong>shining example.&nbsp;</strong></p>
<blockquote>
<p>Sarve Bhavintu Sukhina + well being of all be protected by the powerful</p></blockquote>
<h3>Earlier debate&nbsp;</h3>
<p>CAA = PRO (Hansa mehta, Rajkumar Amrit kaur ) ; AGAINST (MMM, sardar patel) ; BRA = introduce but not impose&nbsp;;&nbsp;</p>
<p>Revived debate&nbsp; = 1980 Shah bano judgement --&gt;&nbsp;Sarla Mudgal Case 1995 (court had held that the religious conversion into Islam by a person from non-Islamic faith is not valid if the conversion is done for the purpose of polygamy.)&nbsp; --&gt; Goa as&nbsp;<strong>shining example (</strong><em>SC 2020)</em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Sarla Mudgal case, 1995 =&nbsp;Parliament to frame a UCC, which would help the cause of national integration by removing contradictions based on ideologies</em></p>
